NNAAMMEE
       MiniLibX - Managing windows

SSYYNNOOPPSSYYSS
       _v_o_i_d _*
       mmllxx__nneeww__wwiinnddooww ( _v_o_i_d _*_m_l_x___p_t_r_, _i_n_t _s_i_z_e___x_, _i_n_t _s_i_z_e___y_, _c_h_a_r _*_t_i_t_l_e );

       _i_n_t
       mmllxx__cclleeaarr__wwiinnddooww ( _v_o_i_d _*_m_l_x___p_t_r_, _v_o_i_d _*_w_i_n___p_t_r );

       _i_n_t
       mmllxx__ddeessttrrooyy__wwiinnddooww ( _v_o_i_d _*_m_l_x___p_t_r_, _v_o_i_d _*_w_i_n___p_t_r );



DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       The  mmllxx__nneeww__wwiinnddooww  ()  function  creates  a new window on the screen,
       using the _s_i_z_e___x and _s_i_z_e___y parameters to determine its size, and _t_i_t_l_e
       as  the  text  that should be displayed in the window's title bar.  The
       _m_l_x___p_t_r parameter is the connection identifier returned by mmllxx__iinniitt  ()
       (see  the  mmllxx  man  page).   mmllxx__nneeww__wwiinnddooww () returns a _v_o_i_d _* window
       identifier that can be used by other MiniLibX  calls.   Note  that  the
       MiniLibX can handle an arbitrary number of separate windows.

       mmllxx__cclleeaarr__wwiinnddooww  ()  and  mmllxx__ddeessttrrooyy__wwiinnddooww () respectively clear (in
       black) and destroy the given window. They both have  the  same  parame-
       ters:  _m_l_x___p_t_r  is  the  screen connection identifier, and _w_i_n___p_t_r is a
       window identifier.


RREETTUURRNN VVAALLUUEESS
       If mmllxx__nneeww__wwiinnddooww(()) fails to create a new window (for wathever reason),
       it will return NULL, otherwise a non-null pointer is returned as a win-
       dow identifier.   mmllxx__cclleeaarr__wwiinnddooww  and  mmllxx__ddeessttrrooyy__wwiinnddooww  right  now
       return nothing.


SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       mlx(3), mlx_pixel_put(3), mlx_new_image(3), mlx_loop(3)


